    diff = np.abs(bins - item)
    return np.exp(-diff / (np.mean(diff) + 1e-8))
```

### Implementation 9: Maximizing Bin Size with Random Perturbation
This function prioritizes larger bins with a small random perturbation to add diversity.

```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    priority = bins
    noise = np.random.normal(0, 0.1, bins.shape)
    return priority + noise
```

### Implementation 10: Maximizing Bin Size with Inverse Proportionality
This function prioritizes bins that are larger than the item, with priority inversely proportional to the bin size.

```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    mask = bins > item
    priority = np.zeros_like(bins)
    priority[mask] = 1 / bins[mask]
    return priority
```

