### Problem Understanding:
The bin packing problem is a well-known optimization problem where you have a set of items of various sizes and a set of bins of fixed capacity. The goal is to pack the items into the bins such that the number of bins used is minimized or some other objective is optimized.

In this task, each function will take an item (its size) and an array of bins (each representing the current state of the bin, perhaps with some items already placed, and the remaining capacity), and return a priority score for each bin, indicating how good it is to place the item into that bin. The heuristic will then select the bin with the highest priority score to place the item.

The function must be a vectorized numpy function, avoiding loops and conditionals where possible.

### Allowed Functions:
