### Implementation 1: Exponential Decay with Standard Deviation
This implementation uses exponential decay based on the difference between the item size and each bin size, multiplied by the standard deviation of the bins.

```python
import numpy as np

def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins)
```

